    "Furthermore, the world map collaboration analysis highlights that developed countries, such as the USA, China, Canada, United Kingdom, Australia, and the Netherlands, are key players in fostering collaborative research on AI for breast cancer diagnosis and treatment through ongoing international partnerships.",
    "As an example, an innovative Computer-Aided Detection (CAD) system utilizing deep learning and computer vision techniques was introduced to enhance breast cancer diagnosis by independently identifying, segmenting, and categorizing breast lesions based on pathology.",
    "Thorough validation using the Curated Breast Imaging Subset of the Digital Database for Screening Mammography (CBIS-DDSM) demonstrated the system's exceptional performance, with a 99% success rate in detecting and classifying breast masses.",
    "The detection accuracy was 98.5%, while the segmentation of breast masses for examination achieved approximately 95.39% performance.",
    "In the final classification phase, the system reached an overall accuracy of 99.16% [37]."
  ],
